Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, @Italian Seasoning{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, trim and cut @zucchini{1}(trimmed and cut into ¼-inch-thick rounds). Pick @basil{1/2%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves. Halve @ciabatta roll{2}. Finely chop @sun-dried tomatoes{1.5%ounce}.

Toss zucchini in a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}, @Italian Seasoning{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini in a single layer; cook until golden brown and just tender, ~{2-4%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> 4 SERVINGS: Toss with a large drizzle of olive oil.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, chopped basil, and @garlic powder{1/2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread a layer of basil sauce onto cut sides of ciabatta.

Fill ciabatta with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, sun-dried tomatoes, and a few slices of zucchini (you may have some left over—feel free to serve on the side, if you like).

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium heat. Once hot, add sandwiches; press down with a #spatula{} or heavy-bottomed pan. Cook, pressing occasionally, until bread is toasted and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, halve on a diagonal.

Divide between plates. Serve with potato wedges on the side.

> 4 SERVINGS: Cook sandwiches in batches if needed.

> TIP: If pan seems dry when flipping the sandwiches, add another drizzle of oil or ½ TBSP butter. Lower heat if bread begins to brown too quickly.